items.description:
Available only to approved renewable energy system members who have completed all necessary applications, agreements and paperwork, passed the necessary engineering reviews and passed the safety test. The rate shall be limited by the availability of appropriate meters and further limited by the percentage of the Cooperative's load served by renewable energy systems and/or impact on the Cooperative's members not utilizing this rate.

This rate is not available for unoccupied properties. Seasonal use properties may have the maximum size of the system limited by a calculation of a occupied load (see system sizing). The renewable energy system shall be sized so that it does not generate more energy than is used by the member on an annualized basis.
items.energycomments: The Tiered Energy Charge is the sum of the Energy Charge, the Power Cost Adjustment (PCA) and the Transitional Energy Facility Assessment Charge (TEFA).
